Package org.aludratest.service.gui.web.selenium.selenium2.condition

Class Summary
AbstractElementCondition<E> Parent class for ExpectedCondition implementations that rely on the presence of a WebElement.
AnyDropDownOptions Collects specific property values of all options of a drop down box.
BooleanCondition Parent class for ExpectedCondition implementations that rely on the presence of a WebElement and return a boolean value.
DropDownBoxOptionLabelsPresence Checks a drop down box for the presence of required entries.
DropDownOptionLocatable Checks the presence of a drop down entry.
ElementAbsence Checks the absence of an element.
ElementEditableCondition  
ElementEnabledCondition  
ElementPresence Checks an element for presence.
ElementValuePresence Checks an element for the presence of a 'value' attribute.
MixedElementCondition Performs a combination of checks on a web GUI element: It always checks for presence and if it is in foreground and can be configured to check for visibility additionally.
NotCondition Negates the given condition for every call to apply().
OptionSelected Checks if an element has a selected option.
StringCondition Parent class for ExpectedCondition implementations that rely on the presence of a WebElement and return a string value.
ValidatingCondition Parent class for ExpectedCondition implementations that validates a text related to a WebElement and uses a Validator.
WebElementCondition Parent class for ExpectedCondition implementations that rely on the presence of a WebElement and return a WebElement value.
WindowPresence Checks the presence of a window.
ZIndexSupport Performs z-index calculations with Selenium 2.
